# Toolchain pins for the sample projects — the single source of truth for both
# `make check` locally and the per-project workflows in .github/workflows/,
# which read the versions out of this file rather than hardcoding them.
#
# Java and Ruby deliberately sit on an older LTS than the monorepo's own ports
# (which track the repo-root .tool-versions): the samples double as proof that
# Varar works on the runtimes consumers are actually on. Ruby is pinned
# per-project in ruby-*/.tool-versions, since it differs from everything else.
#
# Not listed — each is pinned by its own native file, which the workflows read
# rather than naming a version:
#   Rust    rust-cargotest/rust-toolchain.toml          (rustup, cargo)
#   Node    typescript-vitest/.node-version             (setup-node, nvm/fnm)
#   pnpm    "packageManager" in typescript-vitest/package.json  (corepack)
java temurin-25.0.3+9.0.LTS
golang 1.26.3
dotnet 10.0.302
